Definition: a progressive disease of the central nervous system marked by increasing lack of coordination and advancing to paralysis and death within a year of the appearance of symptoms
Example: thought to have been transmitted by cannibalistic consumption of diseased brain tissue since the disease virtually disappeared when cannibalism was abandoned
Synonyms: nervous_disorder, a, progressive, disease, of, the, central, nervous, system, marked, by, increasing, lack, coordination, and, advancing, to, paralysis, death, within, year, appearance, symptoms, thought, have, been, transmitted, cannibalistic, consumption, diseased, brain, tissue, since, virtually, disappeared, when, cannibalism, was, abandoned
Category: noun.state
